  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Wednesday, and today's entry is going to be entirely about our dog, because Perry earned it.",
      "zh": "星期三，今天這篇日記整篇都要寫我們家的狗，因為 Perry 值得擁有這篇。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry is a big brown dog with a long tail that never stops moving, even when he is asleep.",
      "zh": "Perry 是一隻棕色的大狗，有一條長長的尾巴，就算牠睡著了也不會停止搖動。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He is not the smartest animal in the world, but he is probably the happiest one in our whole yard.",
      "zh": "他不是世界上最聰明的動物，但他大概是我們整個院子裡最快樂的一隻。"
    },
    {
      "en": "This morning Perry decided the yard needed a new hole, so he started digging right next to Mom's tomato plants.",
      "zh": "今天早上 Perry 決定院子需要一個新洞，於是他開始在媽媽的番茄植株旁邊挖了起來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time I noticed, he had already dug a hole deep enough to hide half of his own body inside it.",
      "zh": "等我注意到的時候，他已經挖了一個深到能藏住自己半個身體的洞。"
    },
    {
      "en": "His whole face and both front paws were covered in thick brown mud, and he looked extremely proud of himself.",
      "zh": "他整張臉跟兩隻前腳都沾滿了厚厚的棕色泥巴，看起來對自己非常滿意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William thought the muddy hole looked amazing and wanted to jump in and dig with Perry, but Mom said absolutely not.",
      "zh": "William 覺得那個泥巴洞看起來超酷，想跳進去跟 Perry 一起挖，但媽媽說絕對不行。"
    },
    {
      "en": "So Perry got a bath in the backyard, which he clearly did not enjoy, judging by the sad look on his wet face.",
      "zh": "所以 Perry 在後院被洗澡，從他濕濕臉上那副哀怨的表情看得出來他一點都不喜歡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I had to catch him twice because he tried to run away from the water with soap still all over his back.",
      "zh": "我抓了他兩次，因為他背上還沾著肥皂就想從水裡逃走。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After the bath, we wrapped him in a big towel and he ran around the living room to dry himself off, which took about ten minutes.",
      "zh": "洗完澡後，我們用一條大毛巾把他包起來，他在客廳裡跑來跑去把自己弄乾，這花了大概十分鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Once he was dry, his sense of smell brought him straight to the kitchen, where Sophia was cooking chicken for dinner.",
      "zh": "乾了以後，他的嗅覺立刻把他帶到廚房，因為 Sophia 正在煮雞肉當晚餐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry sat by the stove with his nose pointed up in the air, following the smell like it was pulling him on a string.",
      "zh": "Perry 坐在爐子旁邊，鼻子朝上聞著，那個香味好像用一條線在拉著他一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia gave him one small, safe piece of plain chicken, and Perry acted like he had won an award for it.",
      "zh": "Sophia 給了他一小塊安全無調味的雞肉，Perry 表現得好像自己得了獎一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After dinner, William took Perry for a short walk to the park near our apartment building.",
      "zh": "晚餐後，William 帶 Perry 到我們公寓附近的公園散了一小段步。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry pulled on his leash the entire way, excited about every single tree, bird, and stranger's shoe he could smell.",
      "zh": "Perry 整路都在拉著牽繩，對每一棵樹、每一隻鳥，還有每一雙陌生人的鞋子的味道都興奮不已。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the park, another dog owner asked what kind of pet Perry was, since his fur was still a little damp and messy.",
      "zh": "在公園裡，另一位養狗的人問 Perry 是什麼品種的寵物，因為牠的毛還有點濕濕亂亂的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William proudly said Perry was \"a very brave animal who once dug a hole to the other side of the world,\" which was not exactly true.",
      "zh": "William 驕傲地說 Perry 是「一隻曾經挖洞挖到地球另一邊的超勇敢動物」，這話其實不太準確。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When they came home, Perry immediately walked past his clean spot and lay down right in the middle of the kitchen floor.",
      "zh": "他們回家後，Perry 直接走過牠原本乾淨的地方，跑去躺在廚房地板正中間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia stepped over him carefully, muttering that this dog thinks the whole house belongs to him.",
      "zh": "Sophia 小心翼翼地跨過牠，嘴裡念著這隻狗以為整間房子都是牠的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Honestly, at this point, I think she might be right, and none of us really mind that much.",
      "zh": "老實說，到了這個地步，我覺得她大概說得沒錯，而我們也都不是很介意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Tonight Perry is sleeping by my bedroom door, tail still moving slightly, probably dreaming about digging an even bigger hole tomorrow.",
      "zh": "今晚 Perry 睡在我房門旁，尾巴還在微微擺動，大概正夢到明天要挖一個更大的洞。"
    }
  ],
  "quiz": [
